rComments: AMAZING & PHENOMENAL! She is truly an inspiration! She has amazing ideas and appreciates students' stories shared in class. She pushes you to think outside the box. LOVE HER!
She was THE most influential teacher of my entire time at UofT.  She was a gem of an educator, pushed us hard and took us to a whole new level of learning.
An inspired educator and a wonderful woman to know!
The course load was insane. Be prepared to hyperventilate.

The demands of this class were insane, both in the amount of readings, the assignments, and the fact that classes were added in personal time because she fell behind. That being said, she is an amazing and inspirational lecturer and the readings themselves were incredible. She should lecture more and have less presentations.

Don't believe the hype. She barely ever teaches (mostly group presentations), and she has insane expectations (5 novels + a course reader for a half credit course) and she acts as if we should have no problem keeping up, even though most of us are full-time students! Yes, she's as intelligent as everyone claims, but MOST PROFESSORS ARE! Stressful.
Prof. Alexander is excellent. I highly recommend this course or any course taught by Prof. Alexander. Although it was a heavy course it was def. worth while.
